          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "I notice the workspace is currently empty. To implement the module respawning and libselinux-python removal features as described, I'll need the test files and/or the Ansible codebase. \n\nCould you please provide:\n1. The test files that define the expected behavior\n2. The existing module files (dnf.py, yum.py, apt.py, apt_repository.py, etc.)\n3. The SELinux utilities in module_utils\n4. Any test commands or configuration needed to run the test suite\n\nAlternatively, if you'd like me to:\n- Clone the ansible/ansible repository from GitHub, please confirm\n- Or work with specific files you can upload\n\nOnce I have access to the test suite, I'll:\n1. Run the tests first to see what's failing\n2. Understand the exact interface requirements from the test code\n3. Implement the respawn mechanism\n4. Refactor SELinux handling\n5. Verify all tests pass\n\nPlease provide the code files or clarify where I should get them from.",
